Mix crumbs and margarine until well blended. Press firmly onto bottom and up side of 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool completely. Spread about 1/2 of the fudge sauce onto bottom of crust; top with ice cream. Cover; freeze 5 to 6 hours or until firm. Remove pie from freezer when ready to serve. Place marshmallow halves, cut-sides down, on top of pie. Broil 4 inches from heat source 2 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed and golden brown. Drizzle with remaining fudge sauce.